The paper proposes a method for automating the process of analog IC design using reinforcement learning, which involves optimizing circuit parameters to meet certain specifications. This falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as it involves training an RL agent to learn how to optimize circuits. Additionally, the paper deals with electronic design automation (EDA) and optimization, which could fall under the categories of cs.ET (electronic design automation), cs.SY (systems and control), and cs.SE (software engineering). Finally, the paper also discusses the use of machine learning techniques such as Bayesian optimization and grid search, which could fall under the category of cs.LG (machine learning).
